biblical view of marriage and the family gets lost in the throes of pendulum
thinking. Truth tends to lie between extremes, but on this issue unnecessary
rigidness creates an extreme opposite and equal reaction. After a while,&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>WOMEN MENTIONED IN THE BIBLE</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/mankind-anthropology/womens-studies/women-mentioned-in-the-bible/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/mankind-anthropology/womens-studies/women-mentioned-in-the-bible/</guid><description>&lt;style>
